1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,300
welcome back

2
00:00:01,300 --> 00:00:06,400
today we are going to work on the Infinity infrastructure required to enter the UEV tier

3
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:08,866
completing the Relative Quest was easy

4
00:00:08,866 --> 00:00:11,800
but I think we are still not ready for the next tier

5
00:00:11,966 --> 00:00:16,000
there are a lot of things we should fix in our base before going on

6
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:18,233
starting from our lack of fuel

7
00:00:18,366 --> 00:00:19,600
after fixing that

8
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:24,500
ae2 still doesn't have enough power for high speed item transfers

9
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:27,300
but instead of a better power plug

10
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:30,900
I think it's time to craft the neutronium energy cell

11
00:00:30,966 --> 00:00:35,566
and that reminded us that we should probably fix our AE2 cable mess

12
00:00:35,700 --> 00:00:37,166
if that looked clean

13
00:00:37,166 --> 00:00:40,433
it is only because that was the peer to peer network

14
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:42,433
we can't really fix that

15
00:00:42,433 --> 00:00:44,566
but we can make it more manageable

16
00:00:44,833 --> 00:00:47,866
messing with that controller could halt our whole base

17
00:00:47,866 --> 00:00:49,700
so we shall build a new one

18
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,200
the issue is that

19
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,966
if we were to use wireless cables like that

20
00:00:53,966 --> 00:00:57,233
we would waste about half of the connections we can have

21
00:00:57,233 --> 00:01:00,633
so we will still have peer to peer connections

22
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:01,266
however

23
00:01:01,266 --> 00:01:05,400
instead of managing those with cables and a huge subnetwork

24
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:10,433
we just bring those where we have enough space to build a wall of wireless connectors

25
00:01:10,466 --> 00:01:14,366
and there we have the first half of our poorly designed new controller

26
00:01:14,366 --> 00:01:17,666
not only it's not the optimal Hilbert curve version

27
00:01:17,666 --> 00:01:21,100
it also has a whole wasting 900 channels

28
00:01:21,100 --> 00:01:21,566
anyways

29
00:01:21,566 --> 00:01:25,900
we now have a nice wall of wireless connectors ready for use

30
00:01:25,900 --> 00:01:28,666
to which we have to reconnect our whole base

31
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:32,033
each peer to peer segment we had one by one

32
00:01:32,033 --> 00:01:35,300
and we are going to remove as many cables as possible

33
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,066
since those increase the game loading time

34
00:01:38,066 --> 00:01:41,000
after reconnecting everything to the new controller

35
00:01:41,033 --> 00:01:43,766
we can check how much of a mess it looks like

36
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:48,033
and the power usage seems to not even reach 1 ZPM amp

37
00:01:48,033 --> 00:01:51,566
we didn't even need the neutronium energy cell

38
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:54,966
the next thing we are going to need is more circuits

39
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,066
and it looks like our vats can't produce

40
00:01:57,233 --> 00:01:57,966
also

41
00:01:57,966 --> 00:02:01,500
we can switch to a recipe that has 8 times more yield

42
00:02:01,900 --> 00:02:02,633
however

43
00:02:02,633 --> 00:02:05,866
that requires a bacteria which is rather hard to get

44
00:02:06,033 --> 00:02:09,800
it takes 3 minutes with a 7% success rate

45
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:13,633
but we had 8 labs running that stuff for the whole last episode

46
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:15,400
so we got our back covered

47
00:02:15,633 --> 00:02:16,600
by the way

48
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:20,166
there was a better way to duplicate bacteria cultures

49
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:21,533
but we are lazy

50
00:02:21,533 --> 00:02:24,400
now we just have to build a new set of vats

51
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:28,200
stuff some of the fluid we already have in the output to kick start it

52
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:29,433
and we are done

53
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:30,233
however

54
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:32,766
we also want faster circuits

55
00:02:32,833 --> 00:02:35,600
so we built some more assembly lines

56
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:36,566
luckily

57
00:02:36,566 --> 00:02:40,233
we can now copy the input bus settings with a data orb

58
00:02:40,366 --> 00:02:43,666
and then we just expand the input sub network

59
00:02:43,733 --> 00:02:46,600
since we can now mass produce bio circuits

60
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:50,500
we shall also review what kind of circuit we use for each tier

61
00:02:50,666 --> 00:02:54,433
making bio stuff with that recipe used quite some infinity

62
00:02:54,433 --> 00:02:55,766
and we run out of it

63
00:02:55,866 --> 00:02:58,766
so we made three more space mining modules

64
00:02:58,766 --> 00:03:01,066
with a filter to only gather that stuff

65
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,900
to provide the computation

66
00:03:02,900 --> 00:03:05,400
instead of making three more computers

67
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,966
we expanded the old one

68
00:03:06,966 --> 00:03:08,433
and added a network switch

69
00:03:08,433 --> 00:03:12,066
to split the computation between the six mining modules

70
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:13,766
and of course

71
00:03:13,766 --> 00:03:18,033
our ore processing plant couldn't keep up with a single mining module

72
00:03:18,033 --> 00:03:20,033
so we overclocked it further

73
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:21,833
and we added a bunch more

74
00:03:22,566 --> 00:03:26,500
crafting all of that stuff clogged our extruder and our wire mill

75
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:30,200
but instead of improving our extruding capacity

76
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:33,500
we instead worked on a proper component assembly line

77
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:35,200
this will save materials

78
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:37,633
and skip most of the extruding part

79
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:43,433
also doing this will free a lot of space from our general purpose assembly lines

80
00:03:43,766 --> 00:03:45,833
that machine looks really cool

81
00:03:45,833 --> 00:03:48,766
but we will make it vertical to fit a single chunk

82
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:52,100
but this machine could not keep up with our needs

83
00:03:52,100 --> 00:03:54,266
so we overclocked it a bit more

84
00:03:54,766 --> 00:03:58,833
just to the point where it uses as much as one of our blast furnaces

85
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:00,233
speaking of which

86
00:04:00,233 --> 00:04:02,866
after fixing the pollution issue once for all

87
00:04:03,033 --> 00:04:05,000
we shall also upgrade

88
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:08,066
once we have enough to match our power generation

89
00:04:08,066 --> 00:04:13,033
we notice that our battery won't act as a buffer any more than the laser connectors do

90
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:19,700
so after getting a CPU with 160 million capacity and 8,000 cores

91
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:21,900
we start working on a better battery

92
00:04:22,366 --> 00:04:25,100
crafting such a thing will take a lot of time

93
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:27,033
but instead of waiting

94
00:04:27,033 --> 00:04:29,966
we can use that time to improve our base

95
00:04:30,633 --> 00:04:33,366
the first thing that got clogged was our mixer

96
00:04:33,966 --> 00:04:38,600
so we started working on some extra mixers that will share the same inputs

97
00:04:38,833 --> 00:04:41,000
and we pushed those a little bit more

98
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:45,366
next our EBFs stopped working due to lack of oganesson

99
00:04:45,833 --> 00:04:48,833
so we built a couple more matter fabricators

100
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:51,700
and only after the build was complete

101
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:52,633
we realized that

102
00:04:52,633 --> 00:04:55,100
we could have pushed for a double overvolt

103
00:04:55,666 --> 00:04:59,000
or maybe we should have added even more energy hatches

104
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:01,500
we should do more testing next time

105
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:05,900
the next thing we notice is that our cable covering machine is slow

106
00:05:06,466 --> 00:05:09,266
this machine for sure does not lack speed

107
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:12,966
what it lacks of is polyphenylene sulfide sheets

108
00:05:13,233 --> 00:05:17,400
those are passively produced by one of our oldest chemical reactors

109
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,433
which is still running in HV

110
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:23,200
luckily we had a ZPM cable close by

111
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:26,266
which can make it go 200 times faster

112
00:05:26,666 --> 00:05:28,800
the next bottleneck is Electrum

113
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:32,300
here the issue is the speed at which we send it to the furnace

114
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:36,100
1000 items buffer is simply too small

115
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:39,666
so we upgrade to an input crafting buffer

116
00:05:39,666 --> 00:05:42,466
and by the time we complete the operation

117
00:05:42,466 --> 00:05:46,700
we can already see how many items has been queued up inside it

118
00:05:47,033 --> 00:05:51,233
but it shouldn't take too much to complete the task for our current furnace

119
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:54,500
the next bottleneck is the bending machine

120
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:56,300
which has the same issue

121
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:59,300
and it was also having issues with the output

122
00:05:59,466 --> 00:06:02,100
that is due to the buffer limitation of the bus

123
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:04,833
which can be increased with a storage cell

124
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:07,466
now it can unleash its true potential

125
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:10,433
the next thing we notice is crystal SoC

126
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:14,233
we used to make those with a lot of emeralds in a convoluted way

127
00:06:14,233 --> 00:06:16,766
but we can now switch to a better recipe

128
00:06:17,033 --> 00:06:19,866
and we can fix that with our wireless terminal

129
00:06:19,866 --> 00:06:22,066
but after modifying a pattern

130
00:06:22,066 --> 00:06:24,566
we must also restart the crafting

131
00:06:24,833 --> 00:06:26,566
the next thing we notice is that

132
00:06:26,566 --> 00:06:29,266
we are making no progress with circuits

133
00:06:29,433 --> 00:06:31,966
that is due to lack of circuit boards

134
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:34,833
after inspecting our PCB factories

135
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:37,966
we remember that we do not have the perfect overclock upgrade

136
00:06:37,966 --> 00:06:41,633
and that nanites will make those work 10 times faster at best

137
00:06:41,633 --> 00:06:43,100
so we change plan

138
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:45,600
and revert back to using LCR

139
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:48,466
but that requires a lot of extra acids

140
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:50,100
those are passively made

141
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:52,766
and the issue here is about the amount we are stocking

142
00:06:53,266 --> 00:06:55,566
so we increase the size of the tank

143
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:58,466
however filling it will take some time

144
00:06:58,466 --> 00:07:01,433
due to the many steps required for that fluid

145
00:07:01,666 --> 00:07:05,900
so since that is required for the thousands of HV circuits

146
00:07:05,900 --> 00:07:10,966
we can instead do a manual batch of a different circuit that does not use epoxy

147
00:07:11,566 --> 00:07:15,700
and we right away notice the speed at which we make the plastic bars

148
00:07:15,866 --> 00:07:18,233
that was an almost unused recipe

149
00:07:18,233 --> 00:07:21,900
so it was left inside the old HV Fluid solidifier

150
00:07:22,133 --> 00:07:24,766
thanks to our wireless universal terminal

151
00:07:24,766 --> 00:07:26,700
we can quickly multiply the pattern

152
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:28,866
and move it to the bigger solidifier

153
00:07:29,233 --> 00:07:30,100
and with that

154
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:33,233
we have completed our batch of surrogate circuits

155
00:07:33,433 --> 00:07:36,500
but we have to convert those into the generic version

156
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:38,766
possibly without editing patterns

157
00:07:38,866 --> 00:07:41,566
so we add a stocking bus on our press

158
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,900
once we get back to our battery

159
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:47,466
we notice that our laser and our cutting machines are not working

160
00:07:47,666 --> 00:07:51,166
that is due to lack of extreme temperature treated water

161
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:53,800
the issue here was the production speed

162
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:56,266
so we increased the parallel count

163
00:07:56,433 --> 00:07:59,433
and that made the machine need a little bit more of power

164
00:07:59,433 --> 00:08:02,033
so we started using lasers there too

165
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:04,666
but our cutting machine still didn't cut it

166
00:08:04,666 --> 00:08:08,300
so we started working on an ugly convoluted mess to help it

167
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:11,300
and finally we completed our new battery

168
00:08:11,466 --> 00:08:12,033
to use it

169
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:13,700
we have to put it in a box

170
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:16,466
and place it inside our battery multi block

171
00:08:16,666 --> 00:08:19,433
that new battery has quite some capacity

172
00:08:19,433 --> 00:08:21,633
and with our current power production

173
00:08:21,633 --> 00:08:24,266
filling it up will take a couple of years

174
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:26,700
so what did we learn today

175
00:08:26,866 --> 00:08:27,133
yeah

176
00:08:27,133 --> 00:08:32,466
let's not spend too much time trying to craft some weird ancient device

177
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,300
欢迎回来！

178
00:00:01,300 --> 00:00:06,400
今天我们将建设进入UEV所需的无尽基础

179
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:08,866
完成对应的任务很容易

180
00:00:08,866 --> 00:00:11,800
但我想我们还没准备好进入UEV

181
00:00:11,966 --> 00:00:13,133
在继续之前

182
00:00:13,133 --> 00:00:16,000
基地仍有许多事情等着修缮

183
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:18,233
从缺乏的燃料开始

184
00:00:18,366 --> 00:00:19,600
修复后

185
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:24,500
AE仍然没有足够的能量进行高速物品传输

186
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:27,300
并非使用更多电力输入

187
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:30,900
我想是时候制造中子能源元件了

188
00:00:30,966 --> 00:00:35,566
这提醒了我们要解决AE频道的问题

189
00:00:35,700 --> 00:00:37,166
如果这看起来很简洁

190
00:00:37,166 --> 00:00:40,433
只是因为那是 p2p 网络

191
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:42,433
真正解决这个问题很难

192
00:00:42,433 --> 00:00:44,566
但可以让它更易管理

193
00:00:44,833 --> 00:00:47,866
在原来的控制器上搞事情会让整个基地瘫痪

194
00:00:47,866 --> 00:00:49,700
所以我们应该造个新的

195
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,200
问题是

196
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,966
如果我们像这样使用无线连接器

197
00:00:53,966 --> 00:00:57,233
一半的频道将被浪费

198
00:00:57,233 --> 00:01:00,633
所以还是要用 p2p 通道

199
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:01,266
然而

200
00:01:01,266 --> 00:01:05,400
不再是用线缆和庞大的子网来管理

201
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:10,433
我们只需要把这些频道送去一堵无线连接器墙

202
00:01:10,466 --> 00:01:14,366
这是我们不佳设计的控制器的前半

203
00:01:14,366 --> 00:01:17,666
（希尔伯特曲线：能填充满一个平面正方形的分形曲线，如下图所示）

204
00:01:17,666 --> 00:01:21,100
还整整浪费了 900 个频道

205
00:01:21,100 --> 00:01:21,566
不管怎样

206
00:01:21,566 --> 00:01:25,900
我们现在有一堵漂亮的无线连接器墙可以使用了

207
00:01:25,900 --> 00:01:28,666
我们要把它连到整个基地

208
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:32,033
一个一个地替换之前的 p2p

209
00:01:32,033 --> 00:01:35,300
我们尽可能多的移除线缆

210
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,066
因为这会让游戏变卡

211
00:01:38,066 --> 00:01:41,000
将所有东西重新连接到新控制器后

212
00:01:41,033 --> 00:01:43,766
我们可以看看它有多乱

213
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:48,033
用电量似乎连 1A ZPM 都没有

214
00:01:48,033 --> 00:01:51,566
我们甚至不需要中子能源元件

215
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:54,966
接下来，我们需要更多的电路板

216
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,066
看起来我们的培养缸停止生产了

217
00:01:57,233 --> 00:01:57,966
不过

218
00:01:57,966 --> 00:02:01,500
我们可以换成产量高 8 倍的配方

219
00:02:01,900 --> 00:02:02,633
然而

220
00:02:02,633 --> 00:02:05,866
这需要一种相当难以获得的细菌

221
00:02:06,033 --> 00:02:09,800
用时 3 分钟成功率却仅有 7%

222
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:13,633
但是上一集已有 8 个实验室在运行

223
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:15,400
我们后顾无忧

224
00:02:15,633 --> 00:02:16,600
顺便说一下

225
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:20,166
有更好的方法来复制菌群

226
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:21,533
但我们很懒

227
00:02:21,533 --> 00:02:24,400
现在我们只需要建造一套新的培养缸

228
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:28,200
填充一些已有液体来启动它

229
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:29,433
完工

230
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:30,233
然而

231
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:32,766
我们还想要更快地制作电路

232
00:02:32,833 --> 00:02:35,600
所以我们建了更多的装配线

233
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:36,566
幸运地

234
00:02:36,566 --> 00:02:40,233
我们现在可以使用数据球复制输入总线设置

235
00:02:40,366 --> 00:02:43,666
然后扩展输入子网

236
00:02:43,733 --> 00:02:46,600
既然我们可以大量生产生物电路

237
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:50,500
应该斟酌各电压使用的电路板

238
00:02:50,666 --> 00:02:52,533
用那个配方制作生物电路

239
00:02:52,533 --> 00:02:54,433
用了相当多的无尽催化剂

240
00:02:54,433 --> 00:02:55,766
库存已经告急

241
00:02:55,866 --> 00:02:58,766
所以我们又做了三个太空采矿模块

242
00:02:58,766 --> 00:03:01,066
并过滤要收集的物品

243
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,900
为了提供算力

244
00:03:02,900 --> 00:03:05,400
不需要额外三台计算机

245
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,966
扩展一下旧的即可

246
00:03:06,966 --> 00:03:08,433
通过添加网络交换机

247
00:03:08,433 --> 00:03:12,066
来均分六个挖掘模块间的算力

248
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:13,766
当然还有

249
00:03:13,766 --> 00:03:18,033
我们的矿石处理厂连一个采矿模块都跟不上

250
00:03:18,033 --> 00:03:20,033
所以我们给它进一步超频

251
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:21,833
再堆一些机器

252
00:03:22,566 --> 00:03:24,066
为了做这些材料

253
00:03:24,066 --> 00:03:26,500
压模机和线缆轧机都跟不上了

254
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:30,200
但我们不用提升压模产能

255
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:33,500
隆重请出部件装配线

256
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:35,200
这将节省材料

257
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:37,633
并跳过大部分压模部分

258
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:43,433
这样做也将释放大量通用装配线的空间

259
00:03:43,766 --> 00:03:45,833
那台机器看起来真的很酷

260
00:03:45,833 --> 00:03:47,200
但是为了塞进单个区块

261
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:48,766
我们把它做成垂直的

262
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:52,100
但是这台机器跟不上我们的需求

263
00:03:52,100 --> 00:03:54,266
所以我们超频了一点

264
00:03:54,766 --> 00:03:58,833
让它和高炉的用电一样多

265
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:00,233
说到高炉

266
00:04:00,233 --> 00:04:02,866
在彻底解决污染问题后

267
00:04:03,033 --> 00:04:05,000
我们接着升级高炉

268
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:08,066
一旦高炉耗电比得上发电机发电

269
00:04:08,066 --> 00:04:13,033
我们发现电池的容量还没激光仓的大

270
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:19,700
在获得1.6亿容量和8000核的CPU后

271
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:21,900
我们开始研究更好的电池

272
00:04:22,366 --> 00:04:25,100
制作这东西需要很多时间

273
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:27,033
但与其等待

274
00:04:27,033 --> 00:04:29,966
我们利用这段时间来做基建

275
00:04:30,633 --> 00:04:33,366
首先，产能不够的是搅拌机

276
00:04:33,966 --> 00:04:38,600
所以我们做了些共享输入样板的搅拌机阵列

277
00:04:38,833 --> 00:04:41,000
我们用8仓供电

278
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:42,433
接下来

279
00:04:42,433 --> 00:04:45,366
高炉由于缺乏鿫而停止工作

280
00:04:45,833 --> 00:04:48,833
所以我们又造了几个物质发生器

281
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:51,700
但我们在造完后

282
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:52,633
才意识到

283
00:04:52,633 --> 00:04:55,100
我们可以升压两次

284
00:04:55,666 --> 00:04:59,000
或许我们应该增加更多的能源仓

285
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:01,500
下次应该做更多的测试

286
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:05,900
接下来是给电缆套皮的组装机

287
00:05:06,466 --> 00:05:09,266
这台机器肯定不缺速度

288
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:12,966
它缺少的是聚苯硫醚箔

289
00:05:13,233 --> 00:05:17,400
它是由我们最古老的化反被动产生的

290
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,433
它仍在HV电压下运行

291
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:20,733
幸运的是

292
00:05:20,733 --> 00:05:23,200
附近有一条ZPM电缆

293
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:26,266
这可以让它快200倍

294
00:05:26,666 --> 00:05:28,800
下一个瓶颈是琥珀金

295
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:32,300
问题是发配速度

296
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:36,100
1000个物品的缓存简直太小了

297
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:39,666
所以我们将其升级至样板输入总线

298
00:05:39,666 --> 00:05:42,466
在完成置换后

299
00:05:42,466 --> 00:05:46,700
便可以看到有多少材料等待处理

300
00:05:47,033 --> 00:05:51,233
但现在的熔炉应该花不了多长时间就能完成任务

301
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:54,500
下一个瓶颈是卷板机

302
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:56,300
它也有同样的问题

303
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:59,300
它的输出也有问题

304
00:05:59,466 --> 00:06:02,100
这是由于输出总线ME的缓存限制

305
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:04,833
而增加存储单元即可

306
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:07,466
现在它可以释放它真正的潜力了

307
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:10,433
接下来我们注意到的是晶体SoC

308
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:14,233
当时我们大量使用绿宝石配方

309
00:06:14,233 --> 00:06:16,766
但现在我们可以换一个更好的

310
00:06:17,033 --> 00:06:19,866
无线终端可以解决这个问题

311
00:06:19,866 --> 00:06:22,066
但在修改样板后

312
00:06:22,066 --> 00:06:24,566
制作进程也必须重新开始

313
00:06:24,833 --> 00:06:26,566
接下来我们注意到的是

314
00:06:26,566 --> 00:06:29,266
我们在电路方面没有任何进展

315
00:06:29,433 --> 00:06:31,966
那是由于缺乏电路基板

316
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:34,833
在检查了我们的PCB工厂后

317
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:37,966
我们记得它没有无损超频

318
00:06:37,966 --> 00:06:41,633
纳米蜂群最多能让它们工作快10倍

319
00:06:41,633 --> 00:06:43,100
所以我们改变计划

320
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:45,600
重新使用大化反

321
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:48,466
但那需要很多额外的酸

322
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:50,100
它们是被动制造的

323
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:52,766
问题在于缓存的数量

324
00:06:53,266 --> 00:06:55,566
所以我们增加超级缸容量

325
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:58,466
但是填充需要一些时间

326
00:06:58,466 --> 00:07:01,433
由于该流体需要许多步骤

327
00:07:01,666 --> 00:07:05,900
由于终极电池需要上千的HV电路板

328
00:07:05,900 --> 00:07:10,966
我们可以手动批量生产不使用环氧树脂的电路板

329
00:07:11,566 --> 00:07:15,700
我们马上注意到制作塑料的速度

330
00:07:15,866 --> 00:07:18,233
那是一个几乎没有用过的配方

331
00:07:18,233 --> 00:07:21,900
所以它被留在了旧的HV流体固化器中

332
00:07:22,133 --> 00:07:24,766
感谢我们的无线通用终端

333
00:07:24,766 --> 00:07:26,700
我们可以快速倍增样板

334
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:28,866
并将其移动到大固化

335
00:07:29,233 --> 00:07:30,100
有了这个

336
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:33,233
我们已经完成了一批代理电路

337
00:07:33,433 --> 00:07:36,500
但我们必须将它们转换为通用版本

338
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:38,766
最好不要动已有的样板

339
00:07:38,866 --> 00:07:41,566
所以我们在冲压机床上增加一个存储总线

340
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,900
一旦我们重新查看终极电池

341
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:47,466
我们注意到激光蚀刻和切割机不工作

342
00:07:47,666 --> 00:07:51,166
这是由于缺乏五级水

343
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:53,800
这里的问题是生产速度

344
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:56,266
所以我们增加了并行数

345
00:07:56,433 --> 00:07:59,433
这使得机器需要更多的能量

346
00:07:59,433 --> 00:08:02,033
所以我们也使用激光仓

347
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:04,666
但是我们的切割机还是不工作

348
00:08:04,666 --> 00:08:08,300
于是我们动手搞了个丑陋繁琐的怪东西来帮它

349
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:11,300
我们最终完成了新电池

350
00:08:11,466 --> 00:08:12,033
要使用它

351
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:13,700
我们必须把它放在盒子里

352
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:16,466
并将其放入兰波顿电容库中

353
00:08:16,666 --> 00:08:19,433
那个新电容有相当大的容量

354
00:08:19,433 --> 00:08:21,633
以我们目前的电力生产

355
00:08:21,633 --> 00:08:24,266
填满它需要几年时间

356
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:26,700
那么我们今天学到了什么？

357
00:08:26,866 --> 00:08:27,133
是呀

358
00:08:27,133 --> 00:08:32,466
不要花太多时间尝试制造奇异的古代装置

359
00:01:14,366 --> 00:01:17,666
它不仅不是最佳希尔伯特曲线版本

